# Streamlit UI Rules

## Tab Structure (8 tabs, no setup tab)

1. Power Rankings — sortable, color-coded by score tier
2. Team Traits — sortable single-metric leaderboards
3. Cinderella Scores — seeds 9+ only, expandable component breakdown
4. Fraud Alerts — seeds 1–6, sorted by FraudScore desc
5. Matchup Calculator — two-team selector -> win prob, spread, confidence tier
6. Bracket Simulation — Monte Carlo results table (probabilities as %)
7. Bracket Strategies — selector for 8 strategies, Final Four + champion
8. Pick Sheet — plain-text printable bracket, download button

## Controls Policy

- No Streamlit sidebar usage for this app
- No setup/upload/update controls inside the UI
- Inputs are managed via files in `data/` and pipeline runs via CLI (`main.py`)

## Color Coding (score tiers)

- >=75: green (`#1a7f37`) — dominant
- >=60: medium green (`#2da44e`)
- >=45: yellow (`#f59e0b`) — toss-up
- <45: red (`#ef4444`) — weak

## Verdict Labels (from UI_OUTPUT_DESIGN.md Section 4)

Use pre-computed `bracket_matchup_verdicts.json` — no math at render time.

## Alert Formatting

- Cinderella: HIGH (>0.55), WATCH (0.40-0.55), No Signal (<0.40)
- Fraud: HIGH (>=0.60), MEDIUM (0.40-0.59), LOW (<0.40)
